      <acqinfo encodinganalog="541">
         <head>Provenance</head>
         <p> The papers of William H. P. Blandy, naval officer, were deposited in
		  the Library of Congress by the Naval Historical Foundation in 1992. The deposit
		  was converted to a gift in 1998.</p>
      </acqinfo>
      <processinfo encodinganalog="583">
         <head>Processing History</head>
         <p>The papers of William H. P. Blandy were arranged and described in
		  1995. The finding aid was revised in 2009.</p>
      </processinfo>
      <separatedmaterial encodinganalog="544 0">
         <head>Transfers</head>
         <p>Items have been transferred from the Manuscript Division to other
		  custodial divisions of the Library. Phonograph records have been transferred to
		  the Motion Picture, Broadcasting, and Recorded Sound Division. Photographs have
		  been transferred to the Prints and Photographs Division. All transfers are
		  identified in these divisions as part of the William H. P. Blandy Papers in the
		  Naval Historical Foundation Collection.</p>
      </separatedmaterial>
      <userestrict encodinganalog="540">
         <head>Copyright Status</head>
         <p>The status of copyright in the unpublished writings of William H. P.
		  Blandy is governed by the Copyright Law of the United States (Title 17,
		  U.S.C.).</p>
      </userestrict>
      <accessrestrict encodinganalog="506 0">
         <head>Access and Restrictions</head>
         <p>The papers of William H. P. Blandy are open to research. Researchers
		  are advised to contact the Manuscript Reading Room prior to visiting. Many
		  collections are stored off-site and advance notice is needed to retrieve these
		  items for research use.</p>
      </accessrestrict>
      <prefercite encodinganalog="524">
         <head>Preferred Citation</head>
         <p>Researchers wishing to cite this collection should include the
		  following information: Container number, William H. P. Blandy Papers, Naval
		  Historical Foundation Collection, Manuscript Division, Library of Congress,
		  Washington, D.C. </p>
      </prefercite>
      <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
         <head>Scope and Content Note</head>
         <p>The papers of William Henry Purnell Blandy (1890-1954) span the years
		  1913-1977 and consist of correspondence, clippings, speeches, reports,
		  scrapbooks, and miscellaneous biographical material. The focus is on the World
		  War II years when Blandy headed the Naval Bureau of Ordnance and on his
		  direction in 1946 of Operation Crossroads, the atomic tests at Bikini Atoll in
		  the Marshall Islands.</p>
      </scopecontent>
      <arrangement encodinganalog="351$a">
         <head>Arrangement of the Papers</head>
         <p>This collection is arranged alphabetically by type of material,
		  subject, or personal name.</p>
      </arrangement>
